comment:
* Description of a mobile data profile used for establishing
 * data connections.
 *
 * @hide

methods.name: public String getApn()
methods.comment:
* @return The APN (Access Point Name) to establish data connection. This is a string
     * specifically defined by the carrier.

methods.name: public int getProtocolType()
methods.comment: * @return The connection protocol defined in 3GPP TS 27.007 section 10.1.1.

methods.name: public int getAuthType()
methods.comment: * @return The authentication protocol used for this PDP context.

methods.name: public String getUserName()
methods.comment: * @return The username for APN. Can be null.

methods.name: public String getPassword()
methods.comment: * @return The password for APN. Can be null.

methods.name: public int getMaxConnectionsTime()
methods.comment:
* @return The period in seconds to limit the maximum connections.
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public int getWaitTime()
methods.comment:
* @return The required wait time in seconds after a successful UE initiated disconnect of a
     * given PDN connection before the device can send a new PDN connection request for that given
     * PDN.
     *
     * @hide

methods.name: public boolean isEnabled()
methods.comment: * @return True if the profile is enabled.

methods.name: public int getRoamingProtocolType()
methods.comment: * @return The connection protocol on roaming network defined in 3GPP TS 27.007 section 10.1.1.

methods.name: public int getBearerBitmask()
methods.comment: * @return The bearer bitmask indicating the applicable networks for this data profile.

methods.name: public int getMtu()
methods.comment:
* @return The maximum transmission unit (MTU) size in bytes.
     * @deprecated use {@link #getMtuV4} or {@link #getMtuV6} instead.

methods.name: public int getMtuV4()
methods.comment:
* This replaces the deprecated method getMtu.
     * @return The maximum transmission unit (MTU) size in bytes, for IPv4.

methods.name: public int getMtuV6()
methods.comment: * @return The maximum transmission unit (MTU) size in bytes, for IPv6.

methods.name: public boolean isPersistent()
methods.comment: * @return {@code true} if modem must persist this data profile.

methods.name: public boolean isPreferred()
methods.comment:
* @return {@code true} if this data profile was used to bring up the last default
     * (i.e internet) data connection successfully, or the one chosen by the user in Settings'
     * APN editor. For one carrier there can be only one profiled preferred.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)
